Priority: optional
Maintainer: Barak A. Pearlmutter <bap@debian.org>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 4.0.0)
Standards-Version: 3.6.1

Package: raidutils
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Adaptec I2O compliant RAID controller management utilities
 The raidutils program allow the user to manage the Adaptec I2O
 compliant RAID controllers.  It can, for example, create/delete an
 RAID array, add/remove a hot spare drive to/from a RAID array,
 activate/silence the alarm or get information about the status of the
 RAID array and disks.
